I grew into this person , I did not grow up nor was raised this way. 

The rebel of the family , the one that go against all odds. I used to be quiet , shy , avoiding eye contact , interact with people & be happy with whatever life bring….

That’s not the case anymore, I grew into this new person who love to take risk , I.e hang around sharks 🦈, crocodile 🐊, explore one of the most remote places known to man , engage with people with different values & cultures , try different food knowing dang well I’ll most likely be sick after etc…. 

Saying this to let you know , that it’s entirely fine to become whoever you want to be. 

Explore more , hang out with friends , try new experiences outside of your country , build a community around you , Be YOU ! 

By @alivelikethewind 📸

Is India 🇮🇳 on your bucket list ? 

Beautiful, chaotic, colorful, inspiring… @trocalsofficial was the main character of this trip for helping us out and coordinating…

Hear me out : 

Get a visa 

Be Mindful of What You Eat

Visit other cities 

Some cities don’t eat meat , fully vegetarian 

Holi can be a lot and stressful for some people

Drink water 

Get a sim Card 

Be absolutely open minded 

Dress comfortably

A sacred place to be in Govardhan, India 🇮🇳 ; Kusum Sarovar. 

It is believed that Radharani (the love interest of Lord Krishna) used to come to this place to collect flowers, and thus, the name comes - Kusum, which stands for flowers and Sarovar for the pond.

India 🇮🇳 is literally full of stories, if you’re really into exploring & learning this might be the place from myth & legends , you’ll get all the history. 

Photo by the bro @alivelikethewind 📸
Went on a trip with @trocalsofficial 🧳
